<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-153-009 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 785 224</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  May 20 1991 v220 n20 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Outage at Merc won't be the pits. (Chicago Mercantile Exchange'telecommunications backup system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lindstrom, Ann H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Chicago Mercantile Exchange has installed Illinois Bell'stelecommunications disaster avoidance system.andP;  The exchange, whichhas 2,400 telephones and over 10,000 circuits, has a critical needto communicate with it 70 member firms.andP;  The members can avoiddisasters by dividing their telephone lines to the exchangebetween two central offices.andP;  The backup system, which protectsthe local and long-distance dial tone and POTS lines of theexchange, includes data communications, voice communications,carrier access, and 800 number services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Chicago Mercantile Exchange (Communication systems)Illinois Bell Telephone Co. (Services).andO;Topic:     Communications ManagementTelecommunicationsDisaster PlanningBack-Up SystemsCentral Office EquipmentTelecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>